      "content": "# GET /user\n\n## Overview\nRetrieves current authenticated user profile data including unique identifier, email address, and subscription tier.\n\n## Authentication\nRequires a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header or a valid API key in the X-API-Key header.\n\n## Request Parameters\nNo query parameters are required for this endpoint.\n\n## Response Format\nReturns a 200 OK status with a JSON body containing the user object.\n\n## Response Fields\nThe `id` field contains the unique string identifier. The `email` field holds the primary contact address. The `status` field indicates active, suspended, or deleted.\n\n## Error Codes\nReturns a 401 Unauthorized status for invalid or expired tokens. Returns a 404 Not Found status if the user ID does not exist. Returns a 500 Internal Server Error for unexpected backend failures.\n\n## Usage Notes\nEnsure the user session has not expired before making requests. Rate limits apply per minute to prevent abuse.\n\n## Security Considerations\nNever expose sensitive fields like passwords or API secrets in the response payload.",
